The '''yellow-spotted bush sparrow''' or '''yellow-spotted petronia''' ('''''Gymnoris pyrgita''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the sparrow [[Family (taxonomy)|family]], [[Passeridae]].

It is common throughout the [[Sahel]] and the [[Horn of Africa]]. Its natural [[habitat]]s are dry [[savannah]] and subtropical or tropical dry lowland [[grassland]].

